First Read: 22-Jan-26
HJR46 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 COMMENDING CATHY WALLER MCGOWIN AND HER WORK WITH THE
4 ALABAMA WOMEN'S COMMISSION.
5
6 WHEREAS, we take great pride and pleasure in
7 commending Cathy Waller McGowin for eight years of exemplary
8 service as a member of the Alabama Women's Commission; and
9 WHEREAS, Cathy Waller McGowin is a native of
10 Birmingham, Alabama, where she attended Huffman High School,
11 and in 1984 relocated to Mobile, Alabama, with her husband,
12 Dr. Jeff McGowin, as he began his career in orthopedic
13 surgery; and
14 WHEREAS, Mrs. McGowin earned her nursing degree from
15 the Capstone College of Nursing at The University of Alabama
16 in 1980 and was inducted into the Sigma Theta Tau
17 International Honor Society for Nursing; and
18 WHEREAS, she has devoted her professional career to
19 nursing and health care, serving patients in both Jefferson
20 and Mobile Counties in a variety of clinical settings,
21 including Emergency Care, Critical Care, Post-Surgical Care,
22 and Cardiac Rehabilitation; and
23 WHEREAS, in addition to her professional service,
24 Mrs. McGowin has demonstrated a longstanding commitment to
25 community involvement and volunteerism in Mobile County,
26 including service on the Board of Directors for the Junior
27 League of Mobile and the Medical Alliance for Mobile County;
28 and
Page 1

and
HJR46 Enrolled
29 WHEREAS, her charitable work includes volunteering
30 with Camp Rap-A-Hope, an organization providing year-round
31 programs and summer camp experiences for children ages seven
32 through 17 who have or has had cancer, as well as tutoring
33 4th grade students in mathematics through Partners in
34 Education and serving as president of the Parent-Teacher
35 Association at her children's school; and
36 WHEREAS, as an active community volunteer, Mrs.
37 McGowin has chaired fundraising efforts for numerous
38 nonprofit organizations and, together with her husband,
39 served as Club Leader for the University of Virginia Club of
40 Mobile, where she established an annual service project to
41 support local charities; and
42 WHEREAS, in recognition of her leadership and
43 commitment to advancing the status of women, Mrs. McGowin
44 was appointed by Governor Kay Ivey in 2017 to serve as a
45 Commissioner on the Alabama Women's Commission and has
46 served as Chair of the Commission since October 2020; and
47 WHEREAS, during her tenure with the Alabama Women's
48 Commission, Mrs. McGowin has played a key role in advancing
49 impactful initiatives, including the 211KNOW text messaging
50 program, a collaborative study with The University of
51 Alabama examining the effects of parental cell phone use on
52 preschool child development, and the Lunch and Learn program
53 designed for agency leaders across the State of Alabama; and
54 WHEREAS, Mrs. McGowin is also an active member of St.
55 Ignatius Catholic Church, where she has volunteered her time
56 teaching religious education classes to elementary-aged
Page 2

teaching religious education classes to elementary-aged
HJR46 Enrolled
57 children, and was appointed by Governor Kay Ivey in January
58 2023 to serve on the Board of the Department of Child Abuse
59 and Neglect Prevention, further reflecting her dedication to
60 service, faith, and the well-being of Alabama's children and
61 families; and
62 WHEREAS, Mrs. McGowin's life and work exemplify
63 public service, leadership, compassion, and an unwavering
64 commitment to improving the lives of women, children, and
65 families throughout the State of Alabama; now therefore,
66 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
67 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That Cathy Waller McGowin is
68 highly honored and commended for her service as a member of
69 the Alabama Women's Commission, and this resolution is
70 offered in deepest admiration and appreciation, along with
71 best wishes for all future endeavors.
